race.description: Nick Olive Racing Thank You Showcase Mdn Plate
race.comment: ALL ADORE (8) resumes for the sharp Nick Olive yard and was last seen 154 days ago placing at Moruya on debut. Owns a 900m trial win at this venue and draws an inside gate. She will be naturally improved and sets a decent standard. SILK LACE (11) creates plenty of interest on debut. Brings recent trial wins from Hawkesbury and Scone and Costin sticks from the latest. She's likely to jump and run from the inside barrier and is feared. VANTANTE (12) went close at Moruya before spelling but needed the first-up run at Wyong. JVO stays aboard from that, and despite the wide gate we're likely to see an improved effort. BOURBON QUEEN (9) is a local on resumption and has switched from a leading Sydney barn. Hasn't been seen on race day since a solid debut at Newcastle, but despite the wide gate, is worth a market watch.
